  "prompt": "How do I learn spoken English?",
  "response": "Here are some effective ways to learn spoken English:\n\n1. Practice listening\n- Watch English movies, TV shows, and YouTube videos\n- Listen to English podcasts and radio\n- Use language learning apps with audio content\n\n2. Speak regularly\n- Find a language exchange partner online\n- Join conversation groups\n- Practice speaking with native speakers\n- Talk to yourself in English\n\n3. Improve pronunciation\n- Use pronunciation guides and videos\n- Mimic native speakers\n- Practice tongue twisters\n- Record yourself speaking and listen back\n\n4. Take structured lessons\n- Online courses\n- Language learning apps (Duolingo, Babbel)\n- Private tutoring\n- Group classes\n\n5. Immerse yourself\n- Change device language settings to English\n- Read English books and newspapers\n- Think in English\n- Try to use English in daily life\n\n6. Learn common phrases and idioms\n- Study everyday conversational English\n- Learn colloquial expressions\n- Practice using them in context\n\n7. Don't be afraid of making mistakes\n- Embrace errors as learning opportunities\n- Be confident and keep practicing\n\n8. Use technology\n- Language learning websites\n- Mobile apps\n- Online conversation platforms\n\nConsistent practice and exposure are key to improving spoken English.",
